caption: Such good food! They were celebrating their 5th anniversary and had a special on frozen drinks. I've been here a few times but tonight felt different. The staff was even more on point than usual, food was delicious, drinks were refreshing. Highly recommend!

We drove 45 minutes to this place. Read all great reviews and was super disappointed by the experience. Got there and the host wasn’t even nice because we were late to our reservation trying to find parking. Then we waited 15 minutes for someone to come take our order. Then once we ordered fish and pizza the food literally came in 5 minutes. It was hard to believe the food was made that fast. The pizza was OK but there are definitely better places for pizza. I wouldn’t recommend this place... it wasn’t worth the money.

The food was lovely. Pizza is great. Brussel sprout salad was beyond. The view of the bridge is stunning from outside.  Been there twice and each time the service was not good. The staff there ..... seems frantic and are inattentive

Food was good but waiter (tall guy full of sass) has too much attitude and very unprofessional. Hope management would spend the time and effort to train staff better. We had such profound memories of our first time at this place before the pandemic but not planning to go back anytime soon. Shame.

We went to eat at 4:27 pm on March 5th 2021. The place was empty and just us 2 people were there (us)  A lady attended us and she was friendly and respectful. When we sat down another  waiter (male) came and gave us the menus, however while he was taking our order he was organizing the wines, he did even not look at us and he was about 7 feet away from us, he was turning his back on us. We were the only ones in the restaurant but, that waiter did not have a second to look at us and give a good communication to the customer?  They gave us drinks and fast food, it was very delicious, we love pizza and pasta there, but while we ate the waiter did not come to ask us what else we need or if everything is okay? None of them came to check if our glass of wine and water was empty. Even when paying the bill, I had to stop eating, stand up and go to the waiter to tell him that we are done and we want the receipt to pay.  Barano is a good place to eat however the workers at that place seem to not care when there are 2 people in the restaurant I imagine when the place is busy, so careless. The owner or manager should keep checking and observing how the staff are doing their work. I decided to pack our pizza instead of wasting one more minute being there.
I love this place, they have the best Cannolis in town. They have amazing service and the decor is so pretty.
Had an excellent time here, really enjoyed the cocktails and the good food
Good food but way to expensive. Mozzarella was exceptional on Pizza fresh made.

I've ordered from here twice via Seamless/GrubHub, but the food was incredible both times. Between the cacio e pepe ravioli (which was very light and flavorful), focaccia and olive oil (very fresh), and smoked mozzarella - we had to order it again. Hoping to experience it in person when it gets warmer, but look forward to ordering from here again and trying other menu items til then.

Excellent food served in a stunning space that can accommodate both small and large groups. Gracious service and impeccable cooking will make both casual meals and celebrations feel special. Pizza is not to be missed.
Pizza was delicious, friendly staff, good wine and a heater.
I could eat the ‘Nduja pizza for breakfast, lunch and dinner. It’s that good. It’s also extremely messy, but in the best possible way.

I celebrated my PhD this evening in this great place. I am glad to say that we passed a marvelous evening and the restaurant was evidently one of the reasons for that strong event. The waiters  helped in a pleasant style, the cuisine was yummy and my friends were very  joyful. We shall no dout come back again for more events. Thank you very much.

(Translated by Google) One of my new favorite restaurants. Everything I have tasted on the menu has been delicious, the service is always lovely and professional. They have a very good orange wine! Absolutely try the smoked mozzarella, the garlic bread and the Ragu!  (Original) Un de mes nouveaux restaurants favoris. Best chicken parm in Brooklyn
Our favorite eatery in Brooklyn! Great food, great employees. Try the mozzarella! They make the BEST Last Word on Earth !

I would give 0 stars if I could. Customer service is absolutely terrible as they clearly operate their establishment under the mantra that the customer is always WRONG. Ordered the Gluten Free Cacio e Pepe Ravioli for delivery and received a plate of soggy noodles with a note on my container (see photo). Note that the restaurant did not make any contact to call me ahead of time to alert me that they could not make my initial order. Upon calling the manager, he offered zero apology and instead proceeded to ARGUE with me, justifying what I had been sent and the manner in which it was sent. Unbelievable. There are many great Italian restaurants in this neighborhood, and many restaurants in general that understand the value of treating their customers well. Do not bother spending your money here.

loving the vibes. very caesar salad was delicious couldn’t get enough of it lol that crunch croutons yummm. prosciutto’s portion was surprisingly big, and so are the pasta. left with a full tummy, very happy.
Food was outstanding! Chef AL is a master at his craft.  Nice clean air environment.  Great service too

Chef Al goes above and beyond everytime we visit. The food is always exceptional whether it's a staple on the menu or a seasonal item. The staff is always friendly, fun, and warm. We just love Barano's

Been here multiple times - and always a great experience! Fantastic quality Italian food. Their pastas taste fresh and sooo delicious! Pizza Nduja is out of this world. Waiters are always super friendly and pleasant to talk to! Our go to spot near our house! <3

I ordered through Doordash...they forgot my main order and sent only a small pasta. I got a call from the manager who handled the matter in the best way possible. Very good customer service. Food has always been top notch.  EDIT: The manager delivered the missing food himself. Absurdly impressive!
We were pressured to order everything all at once! Guess they were more concerned with the table turnaround then each customer. Smh!

Food was really good, service was bad enough to not return. Tuesday evening, the trio working had a lot on their plate, nothing crazy, hence the 2 stars not 1. That doesn’t excuse being made to feel deprioritized and rushed. From our original server walking away to serve another party mid conversation to the bartender rushing us to decide on an order. I’d chalk it up to the server having a bad day, but he treated all his other tables affably...

The experience here was phenomenal from start to finish. We were seated right away with immediate service. Dawson, our server was extremely attentive and informative without being pushy. The atmosphere combined with Dawson's wonderful personality and charisma made this a top notch dining experience. The bathrooms were spotless and well kept. The food was fast and made to perfection. The presentation was appetizing and the pizza was amazing. I highly recommend this restaurant. I plan on going often.

Wasn’t pleased by the service, but the food was great. Reason being that they seemed so busy that they didn’t pay much attention to the actual table service. TABLE FOR 2 was very small since we ordered quite a lot of food and a Italian spot that makes you pay for starter bread ? 🥖  but overall great Food.!
Fanstasic food. Fast service. Our waiter Keith was the highlight of our visit. We will be back!

Beyond compare pizza's from the simple to the sensational. This is the spot. I love that they offer quartinos of wine which is a 1/3 of a bottle and perfect share if you're working or the perfect pour if you're not. If you're not looking for pizza, the antipasti are amazing too. Everything is. For desert, the butterscotch budhino is not to be missed!
The best pizza!
That was awesome great food ,drink  our food was delicious

Food was delicious will stop by again

The BEST!!! Everyone here is so nice and accommodating!! we got the brussel sprouts, saffron gigli and the bolognese. All were so delicious! If you’re in the area definitely a go to!

Insanely good gluten free pizza here! The staff are so nice and when we’re not vacationing, we eat here at least once a week, if not more!

What great place, trendy, excellent food and staff are supreme. I"be been here a few times and the gluten free pasta is the best I have tasted. It's a popular place, not far from Dominio Park, so enjoy a walk and a bite to eat or vice versa. We also took our dog there today, an 8 year old , whom we got from a shelter just last week. We sat outside and it was a tranquil experience.

Place is nice, they have tables outside. Cocktail was awesome. And pizza, to say that it was good, say nothing. Perfect margarita with delicious prosuto. Frankly, the service was not normal it was greate!

This was our go-to spot for years when we lived in the neighborhood. We were pumped to see them open the patio during Phase 2 to be nostalgic about old times (we even had our engagement celebration here!). It was unfortunate to see when we got there that both drinks & food were being served in plastic and still were charging full price. Update: The cocktails have gone from *great* to *even greater* - Fred The Cocktail Guy certainly has his act together...  Sit at the bar, chat w/ the bartender, and the folks around you, enjoy a glass (or two) of wine and the excellent antipasti. Leave room for the pasta, 'cos it is *stellar*. Seriously, it's Milan-good. So yeah, save space for that.  The place invites lingering, it's the kinda joint where you are tempted to stay for, oh, that extra hour, and then come back again the next day. There is no pressure by the staff, and no urgency to anything - it's all just mellow, and quite happy-making

They release a new menu every few weeks, I get email updates on their new meals and makes me want to go back every time to try  whats new! The drink menu is great. The bartenders are so skilled, each drink is made with precision. Well done Barano!

Best chef!  Chef Al used to cook at two of my favorite restaurants in Manhattan that have since closed. Circo and Le Cirque. He left for Brooklyn to bless the lucky people of that borough. His food is even more delicious and inventive. There is a wood burning oven for pizza. A superb wine list. Creative cocktails. Simply great food. All of the pasta is made in house and the other entrees are marvelous. It seems to be a neighborhood favorite because i not only see a lot of regulars when i gobut i also run into other Manhattanites there from the restaurants that the chef used to cook at. It is a hike from my place to Brooklyn but worth it. There is also outdoor seating during good weather and they took the space next door for a wine store. Thanks Chef Al!

Came here for NYE dinner. They had the regular menu and not a prixe fix, which is always nice.  They also had some NYE specials in addition to the regular menu, which we took advantage of. These included a very tasty champagne, crab arancini, and foie gras aglonotti. Also got their bread plate which was great as well as the meatballs.  The meatballs were the star in my opinion, pretty perfect. The cannoli is a bit weird for me, the filling cream is too thick and filled with dried fruit...It's like a fruit cake.  The shell of the cannoli was really good.  The managment staff and waitstaff worked together to assist with packing up leftovers and ordering dessert since our waiter was very busy.  There was a long wait between apps and the main pasta dish. Not sure if the aglonotti were made upon order or just because it was a holiday. Either way, we understood it was jam packed and just enjoyed the atmosphere. The vibe is lively and fun, definitely a Brooklyn experience.

Really enjoyed my meals here, everyone there is incredibly friendly and helpful. A lot of choices on the menu including probably some of the most underrated pizzas in town. I wish I lived closer by so I could stop by more often.

*Updated-12/16/18*: Have now been back several times. Food, drinks, and especially friendly/knowledgeable service are consistently excellent! This lovely restaurant has outdoor seating, bar tables and a dining room. It seems to have been discovered by the neighborhood in a good way. I saw romantic couples, families, large groups and singles. I discovered this place.because the chef was at my favorite restaurant in midtown mamhattan for over ten years. We are so happy that Chef Al found a space with better rent even though it is in another borough. Also the drinks and wine list is good and i love the cannollo for dessert.

As an Italian who comes from the Napoli area and lives in NYC, discovering such a great place that bears the name of a location in the island of Ischia has been a pleasure. My wife and I come to Barano once a month. It’s located in Brooklyn and it’s easy to reach. The cuisine has no equal in NYC and it’s our favorite place. You can taste what I would call a modern Italian cuisine as the chef is able to combine traditional Italian dishes with modern, tasteful tricks that make it special. We love their pizza: thin crust with zucchini flowers (I’m sure this is a seasonal dish). Also try the smoked mozzarella with tomatoes and other vegetables. The staff is very nice and is able to suggest the best wine given your meals. They really know about wines so feel free to ask any kind of questions. I had the chance to talk to the chef once (I forgot the name! Pardon!) as I was interested in knowing his background. And that’s when I found out he is an Italian American whose grandparents came straight to Brooklyn from Barano, this lovely neighborhood in Ischia. It’s a must-go location. Enjoy!
Outstanding service with unbelievable food and great price

Italian food never tasted so good. Chef Al’s plates leave you drooling in your sleep and wanting you to come back for more! The restaurant itself is a masterpiece, and is paired perfectly with the unique plates; Not to mention the cocktails have their own personality and make you want to try the others. The music is great, the environment is both fun and romantic with impeccable staff. Great find!

The food is exceptional.  Everything!

Good service, good wine...very overcooked pasta ! I don’t understand how an Italian restaurant can serve such soggy pasta at such prices. It was disappointing to say the least. Also, it has a very New Jersey crowd.

My favorite Italian place in NYC.  Chef Al updates classic recipes with better ingredients and perfect technique, featuring a wood oven. I can’t get enough of his lamb ribs with honey & heat. I always share a pizza.  Plus the wine list is fantastic.

What an experience! From the ambience to the service to the food, I will absolutely be returning! The bar is GORGEOUS,  immaculate. I didn't get the bartender's name, but he was incredibly kind and knowledgeable. My wine knowledge = I like white.  So thankful for Jason, who helped me out with beers and wine, talk about knowledgeable! His passion for drinking is palpable and I appreciate his level of commitment. He mentioned the wine list is always rotating small batches of delicious wines. Also, overheard someone say the cocktails are Beastie Boys-themed! The food, my god, the food! The scallops are to DIE FOR, I was nearly moved to tears! The pasta, one has wild boar, another is red, a little spicy with hints of honey 👅👅 SO GOOD. Also, the veggies!! Whether you get them grilled or pickled (on the side of the delicious fresh mozzarella cheese and prosciutto), they know how to make vegetables absolutely devine. And fried cheese balls! You really can't go wrong with anything on the menu.

The atmosphere is an odd balance of formal and casual and doesn't strike a perfect balance between the two. What matters most is the food, though. The meatballs are delicious, as are the pasta dishes. The much-hyped pizza, however, is no better than okay. There are many better pizzas in town (Marta, Posto, Arturo's, Juliana's) and these need serious improvement if they are to continue being such a major component of the dinner menu. The mozzarella choices are a bit precious but also delicious. The stracciatella came in a bowl, which proved very awkward for serving (just put it on a plate, please). Wines were good, as were coffees and desserts, and our waitress was professional and courteous. I probably won't return, but I enjoyed my meal here. Skip the pizza if you go.

Loved Barano!  Very cool mix of old school southern Italian food paired with some of the latest food trends (just the right amount).  More house-made, hand-pulled mozzarella, please! Five stars for sure!
The food is great, very cozy with beautiful ambience.  The waiters and hostess are very attentive. The food presentation is everything.  One of my favorite restaurants in Williamsburg.
this place was excellent!!! the service and food was out of this world, no complaints, I definitely recommend this place

I love this place! I have been here twice and sat at the bar both times. I started off with the salted mozzarella both times and it is some of the best mozz I've ever had. My first visit I had the octopus to start and then the tagliatelle. The second time the meatballs and tortellini. Still can't decide which I loved more. Have not had the pizza or main dishes yet but plan to on my next visit.
Great tasting antipasto!
Really good, worth a try
OMG THE BEST PLACE EVER!!!!! I LUV THEIR PIZZA!!!!

Wanted to try this place since it opened a few months ago in the South Williamsburg neighbourhood where I live. The atmosphere is nice and it's a really nice setting - that gets it the extra star. Unfortunately, everything else is pretty dire: the food - our party of four ordered a pesto pasta dish, an octupus pasta and assorted starters. In all three cases the food was seriously average and certainly not worth $20 a dish. The octopus in particularly tasted like a tinned tomato and frozen calamari that you could get for about $5. As other people have said, with some of the other food they were trying adventurous stuff and using lots of abstruse Italian words on the menu to justify charging more for the dishes. (incidentally, truffle pasta for $70 anyone? It costs half to a quarter of that all over town). The service was even worse. We got as waitor some guy who looks like Kelly Jones from the Stereophonics. He looked surly all night until we were about to leave when he of course suddenly became fawning. When he brought that bill, we thought we had been overcharged. To be precise - the menu was poorly written: it says "Antipasto tasting - Mozzarella + Salume + Verdure 25, with Mangalica +5". This apparently means that you can SUBSTITUTE the salume for the mangalica by paying $5 more. This was very unclear and we explained this but Kelly Jones insisted that he had explained this and that we were too dim to understand. His manner was very rude and abrasive. Service - bad; food - bad. Why bother going here?
Awesome... Just.Awesome. A must try if you're in the area.

I just came to know that there was a new Italian restaurant in Williamsburg... as a good Italian living abroad I went to try it myself with my wife. The atmosphere and service were great and the food was excellent. We were so intrigued by the menu that we tried many dishes, too many for our stomaches! Everything was excellent, the stracciatella, the eggplant lasagna and the fusilli were fabulous. The wine list was excellent as well and we enjoyed our choice suggested by the sommelier. We will be back
This place is fire. Food is Amazing and Service is second to none. The manager hooks it up and knows his stuff. Need to come here more often.
The food is terrible and the service even worse

New restaurant with potential but falls short. Will say the service and atmosphere are good, but the food tries too hard. Pastas are original but just a little too weird and apps just uninspired. Also - they make you cut your own pizza with clippers, super awkward and results in a large loss of toppings.
Pretty awesome for Italian food in Williamsburg. Riberosa's 2nd restaurant, and just like their NOLITA outpost the pizza is amazing. The pasta was pretty damn good too. Rivals Lilia in my opinion.
Loved the seltzer

Last night I had an amazing evening. The wine selection was great. Enjoyed a three course meal starting with the mozzarella antipasto, followed by two pastas bucatini and the cavatelli then we split the lamb leg. Great experience great to see these types of restaurants are coming to the neighborhood.
Great service. Awesome homemade mozzarella. Didn't try the pizzas but the goat & rabbit pastas were beautiful. One was overdone by the amount of cheese but tasty none the less. Great wine selection.
Went in for dinner last weekend. Great pizza! Charcuterie platter was insane.  We split the pizza and whole fish. Service was good. Wine list was very extensive. Can't wait to go again!
Great food, a bit noisy and ok service. We had the mozzarella cheese (3 different  variations) as an appetizer share. It was heavenly! I recommend to book in advance.

The service didn't seem to match the menu they were going for. The staff was dressed pretty casually and some went even beyond casual. The waiter was very kind but was not knowledgeable of the menu and couldn't make recommendations. It was SUPER cold, pretty loud, and the music was also quite loud. I wouldn't necessarily call this a romantic spot- the table set up is weird and not very intimate. The few booths they have are saved for large parties. The mozzarella was extremely impressive - you basically can't go wrong with the tasting menu. I found the appetizers to be a bit odd and disappointing , especially following such a great appetizer. The pasta was unremarkable and I would not order it again. Meatballs were good, kale was odd, and the octopus was under seasoned. I'd come back but only for wine and cheese.

not italian for sure, american italian yes. the pizza was not good. motorino up the street makes real pizza. overall the dinner was not bad but i would suggest them to be more authentic because there is need of a good italian restaurant in the hood. the decor is nice and the bar large.
LOVE it. Just the appetizers end up being a full meal for my date and i. Great service. Our italian waiter was delightful. Great restaurant. 👍👍
Still early so they're figuring stuff out. Mozzarella, meatballs, and pasta were all great. Pizza was average.
